    {
        "user": "UCS1K3QTH",
        "type": "message",
        "ts": "1708434463.683899",
        "client_msg_id": "C59442D5-0FF4-4B11-A93C-94312B4EAE96",
        "text": "It is hard to remember what the world was like prior to the explosion of smartphones ",
        "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_profile": {
            "avatar_hash": "af83411b2f9d",
            "image_72": "https:\/\/avatars.slack-edge.com\/2018-09-11\/433010126754_af83411b2f9d3dc221a8_72.jpg",
            "first_name": "Stephen",
            "real_name": "Stephen De Gabrielle",
            "display_name": "Stephen De Gabrielle",
            "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
            "name": "spdegabrielle",
            "is_restricted": false,
            "is_ultra_restricted": false
        },
        "thread_ts": "1708096398.023089",
        "parent_user_id": "UCS1K3QTH",
        "blocks": [
            {
                "type": "rich_text",
                "block_id": "arok1",
                "elements": [
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "It is hard to remember what the world was like prior to the explosion of smartphones "
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "user": "U04717WKH5K",
        "type": "message",
        "ts": "1708435361.630199",
        "client_msg_id": "87a35aa6-141d-4a6c-a530-6ca6dcca3c0d",
        "text": "&gt;  the resistance to programming was because of bad tools or that the manual alternatives were sufficient\nI think there were a lot of factors that overlapped -- certainly many workplace systems were literal translations of existing paper forms and offered little in the way of opportunity, but I'd think that the novelty was as much of a factor. It's a huge leap to start thinking computationally. I remember my wife taking a required Excel class when getting her Masters' in Education in the 90s and watching her use a pocket calculator on the desk to sum a column instead of using `=SUM(A1..A10)` and (even more) her resistance to approaching the problem in this way.",
        "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_profile": {
            "avatar_hash": "g415c1650fb0",
            "image_72": "https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/415c1650fb0f17d5a8b182fa4f4d17d7.jpg?s=72&d=https%3A%2F%2Fa.slack-edge.com%2Fdf10d%2Fimg%2Favatars%2Fava_0015-72.png",
            "first_name": "brett",
            "real_name": "brett g porter",
            "display_name": "brett g porter",
            "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
            "name": "brett130",
            "is_restricted": false,
            "is_ultra_restricted": false
        },
        "thread_ts": "1708096398.023089",
        "parent_user_id": "UCS1K3QTH",
        "blocks": [
            {
                "type": "rich_text",
                "block_id": "X37rs",
                "elements": [
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_quote",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " the resistance to programming was because of bad tools or that the manual alternatives were sufficient"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "I think there were a lot of factors that overlapped -- certainly many workplace systems were literal translations of existing paper forms and offered little in the way of opportunity, but I'd think that the novelty was as much of a factor. It's a huge leap to start thinking computationally. I remember my wife taking a required Excel class when getting her Masters' in Education in the 90s and watching her use a pocket calculator on the desk to sum a column instead of using "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "=SUM(A1..A10)",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " and (even more) her resistance to approaching the problem in this way."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
